commit.message: replaced g_queue_pop_tail() with g_queue_pop_head() in falgnfq-loop.c
In falgngfq-dump.c, a "sprintf" is removed and "fprintf" is replaced by "fputs"
remove function "getcwd" from falgnfq-dump.c
Use both source host and source port as hash key
Fix segmentation fault when not using TCP
Drop unused struct declaration from falgnfq-tcp.h
Update TCP packet processing framework and support sending SYN-ACK
Move all casting macros to falgnfq-private.h
Show package version and date in the program
Use git-version-gen from autoconf to generate version numbers
Ignore SIGPIPE and use sig_atomic_t instead of int in the signal handler
Fix possible memory leak
fix "==" and "&" precedency bug in falgnfq-dump.c

Prepare for TCP support
Destination host IP address and port are also needed
LIBNETFILTER_IS_VERY_BUGGY -> LIBNETFILTER_QUEUE_IS_VERY_BUGGY

Support debug level setting
Workaround wrong nfq_ip6_snprintf() in libnetfilter_queue
Add .gitignore
Show ICMP and ICMPv6 in debug message

Prevent using uninitialized variable
Use explicit type conversion to suppress compiler warnings
Fix wrong argument type for queue_num
Drop all trailing tabs
write a dump function to dump internet packet
Add the missing return value
Add signal handler in debug mode to test memory leak
Use a hash table and packet lists instead of a single packet buffer
"IPV4" , "IPV6" allowed when entering parameter.
Workaround broken nfq_udp_get_payload_len() in libnetfilter_queue
Debug message rework
Add --disable-debug configure option
Fix several bugs found by clang static analyzer
Fix unintended hard-coding of queue number 0
Add UDP support code and TCP dummy code
Add missing quoting in autogen.sh
